this command wont make a chart, will make an ephemeris
    pyph -j 2447681.328358219
    if -j is precisely a new moon, then Planets.jaimini_karakas() will fail
    this would probably also happen in two planets had the exact same longitude to 3 decimals
    to sort, they are stored in a dictionary where longitude is the key, Planet is the value. so when two
    planets are at the same longitude, the second planet gets erased in the dictionary. so on a new moon, there
    will not be a Sun is the returned list, since it will have gotten erased by the Moon
    so perhaps i need to switch these so i know the keys will be be unique, then at a test for equality and then decide what to do

